# Naming convention is a set of rules to follow when naming tables and columns in SQL.

## General Rules 
####- Never use SQL reserved keywords(e.g. select, table, user) as identifiers.
####  If an entity is a user, name the table dim_user or account to avoid syntax errors and the need for brackets or double quotes
#### - No Special Characters: Avoid spaces, hyphens, or dots in names. Stick strictly to alphanumeric characters and underscores to
